              Guide Details</font></b></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2">
              </td>
          </tr>

<tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><img border="0" src="../triangle.JPG"><font size="3" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>TREANTS</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Group / Solo:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Solo - Necromancer</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Mob Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">23 to 27</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Zone:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Karana, South</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Location:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">+1500 -3500</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Character Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">29 to 31</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Strategy:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Evil characters only.
<br><br>
Every necro hunts the treants in South Karanas at some point in their career.  The XP and loot is just too good to pass up.  However, by 30th level, the XP drops significantly if you're in a group.
<br><br>
However, you can solo this spawn if you do it right.  And even at 30, the XP is great when you solo.
<br><br>
Make sure you have Allure of Death up and running at all times.  It's all about mana management.  Buff yourself and your pet and med to max.
<br><br>
Cast Screaming Terror on the left one.  If it's resisted, you have one more chance before you need to Feign Death.  If it's not, then send in pet to the RIGHT one and immediately cast fear.  Again, you need fear to stick, so cast until it does.  You have 3 tries to get it before Screaming Terror wears off.  If you don't get fear to stick, Feign Death and let them kill your pet.
<br><br>
Usually, I get Screaming Terror to stick first try.  And I usually get Fear to stick first try as well, so things aren't as bad as what I painted above.  Just be aware.
<br><br>
So, the left one is mezzed and the right one feared.  Start nuking with Shock of Poison on the right one.  By the time he gets out of range, fear should be wearing off and the left one will be waking up.  If you've done this right, you and the battle are completely out of agro range.  If not, cast Screaming Terror again on the left one.
<br><br>
By this point, your pet is pretty beat up, you're down 2 bubbles of mana, and the treant is at 40% health.  Nuke twice more and he dies.  Send your pet into the left one and nuke him fast.  You should end up with 2 bubbles of mana (or slightly less).  Sit down and med.  You've got 3 minutes to get back to full and you may need to heal your pet :-)
<br><br>
If you like to live dangerously, you can take them on two at a time over and over.  However, you can space it out IF the mem blur aspect of Screaming Terror kicks in.  If the left treant doesn't immediately agro on you, then sit down and med for 1.5 minutes, stand up and kill it.  With the spawn broken, you can easily keep up with it solo.
<br><br>
If you ever have a crowd around you when you break the spawn, be prepared for lots of "oooohs" and "aaaahs" and "necro's need to be nerfed" comments :-).  No other class can solo this spot at this level.</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Author:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Eloina Pyromancer (Cazic Thule)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rating:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>9</b> (average of <b>3</b> votes)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rate this spot:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><FORM ACTION = "ratehg.asp" METHOD = post><SELECT NAME="Voting"><OPTION VALUE="0">Rate this Spot</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="1">1 - Don't even bother</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="2">2</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="3">3</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="4">4</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="5">5 - It is ok</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="6">6</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="7">7</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="8">8</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="9">9</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="10">10 - You must come here</OPTION></SELECT><INPUT TYPE = "hidden" NAME = "intHGID" VALUE = 89><INPUT TYPE = "submit" VALUE="Rate It!"></form></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing